# Test runner manifest detection only checks the WORKSPACE ROOT —
# it never walks up. A common dev layout has the user open a
# sub-package inside a larger monorepo (Go module at /repo/go.mod,
# editor opened at /repo/cmd/foo) — in that layout `:go.test` will
# toast "no go.mod" even though one exists upstream.
#
# This .test asserts the current (regressive) behavior so a fix
# is detectable.

# Create a manifest at workspace root, then "open" a subdir as if
# the workspace were that subdir. We can't change the workspace
# mid-test, so we approximate by NOT placing the manifest at root.
write src/main.go "package main"

# Try go.test — there's no go.mod at the workspace root, so it
# should toast. (Confirms detection is root-only.)
command go.test
expect screen contains "no go.mod"

# Same shape for pytest:
write src/test_app.py "def test(): pass"
command pytest.run
# pytest fails-open because it accepts `tests/` too; but with no
# `tests/` dir AND no pyproject AND no setup.py, it toasts.
expect screen contains "no pyproject"
